removal (i.e., via forward Na
exchange). We model the subspace as
a single compartment comprising 2% of the total volume of the myocyte
into which both L-type Ca21
channels and RyR open (see Appendix for
-Ca21
derivation of subspace volume). Immunoﬂuorescence of the Na
