Simulation protocols
During pacing, a stimulus of ␀80 mA/mF is applied for a duration of 0.5 ms.

(49).
The model is paced with a conservative current stimulus carried by K
A discrete time step of 0.0002 ms is used during computation of the AP (or
during voltage clamp simulations) and 0.002 ms during the diastolic interval.
APD is measured as the interval between the time of maximum upstroke
velocity (dV/dtmax) and 90% repolarization (APD).

