Irel

Rates of RyR activation and deactivation were increased from those based
on lipid-bilayer studies in the original publication of Fill et al. (39) to ac-
count for differences in temperature and to create an SR ﬂux that generates a
time course and magnitude of the CaT that closely ﬁt experimentally re-
corded values. For this reason, the rates were not increased uniformly. The
activation rate a1R was increased 3.5 times, and a2R, a3R, and a4R were in-
creased seven times. The deactivation rates b1R, b2R, and b3R were increased
ﬁve times and the deactivation rate b4R was increased 25 times.

