Derivation of subspace volume

We assume a myocyte with a radius of 11 mm and length of 100 mm with
Z-lines spaced by 1.85 mm. T-tubules protrude into the myocyte along the
Z-lines with spacing of 1.5 mm. With these values, we compute 54 Z-lines
per myocyte with 46 t-tubules per Z-line for a total of 2484 t-tubules
per myocyte. The diameter of each t-tubule is 0.3 mm and the distance be-
tween the SR membrane and the t-tubule is 0.02 mm (15). The volume of
subspace along the length of a single t-tubule to the center of the myocyte is:



